Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.25,0:00:15.33,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.29,0:00:25.46,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I feel bad for the people at Globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.29,0:00:28.42,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,They don't know that you're the one
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.79,0:00:32.42,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,choosing all the participants in the Kivotos Plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.82,0:00:34.63,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.43,0:00:38.10,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I feel bad for CEO Kube.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.48,0:00:43.87,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he never even dreamed \Nthat we were using him...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.18,0:00:51.51,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Albion may have an attachment \Nto his avatar body.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.70,0:00:54.99,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.79,0:01:00.07,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,This is a ten-year-old photograph of a \NSeton Company research facility
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.07,0:01:01.95,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,in the Hawaiian Islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.61,0:01:08.50,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It was cleverly hidden, but they're \Na Macbeth Enterprises subsidiary.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.94,0:01:10.22,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,These two.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.90,0:01:22.01,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We believe they are the two \Nthat attacked yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.57,0:01:25.30,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Then it was indeed Macbeth Enterprises.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.72,0:01:28.59,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,These two are designer children, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.59,0:01:32.15,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,And they were overseas during the Kanda incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.57,0:01:37.74,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Then all six that were taken in, \Nexcept Teppei Arashi, are missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.19,0:01:41.66,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Just like Teppei, the other designer children
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.66,0:01:45.31,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,can use the Machine Goodfellows \Nto become Kiltgangs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.18,0:01:49.34,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,I think the fact that the Kiltgangs \Nhave entered their active phase
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.27,0:01:53.71,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,suggests that their preparations are complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.39,0:01:57.22,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't they attack more frequently?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.87,0:02:01.48,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,When Teppei became a Kiltgang,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.48,0:02:05.22,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Hana used the energy built up in the Blume.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.88,0:02:07.06,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei says that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.30,0:02:13.94,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,the craft equivalent to the Kiltgang \Nmothership is orbiting Uranus.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.92,0:02:18.53,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,They've run out of energy, and can't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.53,0:02:21.55,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,So they're using the Machine Goodfellows
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.55,0:02:26.25,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,to get the energy they need \Nfrom the people of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.90,0:02:30.46,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The human libido... Orgone energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.97,0:02:34.42,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, we won't notify HQ about this yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.56,0:02:40.59,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,If Salty Dog learns about the relationship between \Nthe Machine Goodfellows and the Kiltgangs,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.04,0:02:43.42,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,they might decide to detonate \Na nuclear bomb themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.93,0:02:47.60,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,in Tokyo, where Macbeth has offices, \Nand blame it on terrorists.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.95,0:02:51.52,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And even if that saved the rest of humanity,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.44,0:02:55.92,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,you wouldn't accept it, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.58,0:03:01.49,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.04,0:03:06.99,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,it's peculiar that word of such a huge danger \Nhasn't leaked to the public yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.44,0:03:10.55,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,During the Cuban Missile Crisis...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.59,0:03:14.40,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The media said that if the Russians
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.40,0:03:18.55,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,brought nuclear missiles to Cuba, \Nit would incite a full-scale nuclear war.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.08,0:03:24.81,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, the Soviets gave in, \Nand the danger was averted.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.81,0:03:26.76,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Publicly, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.35,0:03:33.19,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,In truth, however, the Soviets had already \Nsent over one hundred missiles there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.19,0:03:37.83,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Only the President and a few \Nof his close advisors knew,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.83,0:03:42.91,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,and the truth wasn't revealed until \Nthirty years after the Cold War ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.46,0:03:47.87,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,It's strange that news of such a dire \Nthreat never leaked to the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.48,0:03:54.24,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Why tell the public they might \Nhave only five minutes to live?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.25,0:03:59.21,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,If a thing is truly dangerous, it's kept secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.28,0:04:02.46,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Throughout history, that's happened many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.34,0:05:40.15,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Ta-da!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.65,0:05:42.27,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Snack time!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.71,0:05:44.60,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Watermelon again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.60,0:05:45.74,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.95,0:05:48.28,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.16,0:05:52.83,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Times like these won't continue for much longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.28,0:06:00.38,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Pitz was saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.03,0:06:03.50,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's nice you can talk to Pitz.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.27,0:06:06.09,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It makes you seem like a heroine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.29,0:06:15.39,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,If even a single Kiltgang makes it to Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.88,0:06:19.48,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,it will drain all humanity of their libidos.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.16,0:06:22.40,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I think so, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.27,0:06:29.99,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,When I first sensed them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.43,0:06:32.41,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I had this awful feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.18,0:06:35.87,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if we need him, we have Teppei.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.29,0:06:40.23,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, if I become a \NKiltgang again, I don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.23,0:06:41.91,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,if I'll return to who I am now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.91,0:06:45.95,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, we shouldn't underestimate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.18,0:06:51.43,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't the Planetary Gears try \Nto make you fire the Livlaster
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.92,0:06:55.03,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,because they wanted infinite energy, Hana?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.03,0:06:55.93,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.51,0:07:00.45,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,And none of them can fire the Livlaster?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.45,0:07:01.48,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.41,0:07:07.44,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.44,0:07:11.82,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,we're pretty amazing, talking about this \Nstuff while eating our watermelon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.24,0:07:13.82,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,We are, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.46,0:07:15.83,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,And get this... I have melons, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.22,0:07:16.91,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Melons!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.34,0:07:18.20,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Melons?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.60,0:07:20.71,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But the melons are for tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.94,0:07:22.33,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.59,0:07:24.00,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.79,0:07:29.03,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow, let's all eat together again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.42,0:07:37.39,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,For now, why not eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.39,0:07:38.68,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Melons...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.04,0:07:41.20,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Pitz?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.20,0:07:43.32,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I saved the seeds, Pitz.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.33,0:07:49.97,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Pitz?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.20,0:07:53.82,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The Kiltgang are going to act?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.24,0:07:56.46,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,"Soon," he says.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.00,0:07:57.66,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Who says?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.19,0:07:59.12,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Pitz.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.12,0:08:00.83,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The squirrel?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.60,0:08:07.13,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,At the moment, there's no \Nsign of any AEO or NEO.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.64,0:08:10.66,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,He says he knows the rough \Ntime and the location
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.66,0:08:12.34,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,where the Orgone energy will be used.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.18,0:08:16.35,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we request a nuclear strike on this area?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.83,0:08:18.92,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,They aren't there yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.92,0:08:21.35,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,But they'll act tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.69,0:08:24.85,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.85,0:08:29.19,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Daichi Manatsu is standing by \Nin the Earth Engine's cockpit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.34,0:08:32.32,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,The Earth Engine is fixed now, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.41,0:08:34.91,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,What are you thinking, Daichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.35,0:08:37.93,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I learned the basic controls in the simulator.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.78,0:08:39.66,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Science Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.09,0:08:43.16,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,His Earth Driver training was ordered by HQ.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.62,0:08:45.66,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,He's been doing it for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.33,0:08:49.25,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,How will that stopgap training help?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.56,0:08:51.16,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You almost died twice...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.16,0:08:52.49,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.83,0:08:54.92,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.35,0:08:59.72,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I'm really scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.26,0:09:02.99,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I'm only a teenager.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.06,0:09:07.46,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But if I don't defeat them,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.46,0:09:09.36,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,we have no hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.42,0:09:13.99,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,And hope is only born of choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.65,0:09:20.93,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Please begin the launch sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.43,0:09:36.59,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The lights of these foolish people...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.59,0:09:41.35,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I can't imagine that Albion \Nwould betray us for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.35,0:09:46.06,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Can you even imagine not being immortal?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.42,0:09:48.02,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.45,0:10:00.41,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,This really is the greatest!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.02,0:10:05.25,Default,Girls,0000,0000,0000,,AEO sighted... It's a Kiltgang.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.64,0:10:09.00,Default,Girls,0000,0000,0000,,Manifestation point in Gamma sector, \Ninside defensive zone 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.49,0:10:11.30,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,It really did appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.30,0:10:12.86,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.86,0:10:16.69,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Is this predictive ability your singularity?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.69,0:10:18.59,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Pitz told me, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.40,0:10:21.22,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Pitz doesn't lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.99,0:10:25.97,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The ability to predict the use of Orgone energy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.53,0:10:28.10,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Pegasus rocket taking off.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.98,0:10:55.21,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The Earth Engine's energy is charging!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.60,0:10:57.42,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The Pegasus rocket is purging Earth Engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.73,0:11:06.56,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Engine, expand!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.30,0:12:26.01,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,The one from the first time?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.06,0:12:34.55,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Engine has made contact with the Kiltgang!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.55,0:12:35.56,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Its attacks aren't hitting!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.17,0:12:38.32,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,If it could land a hit, we could shoot it down...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.32,0:12:40.23,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Abreaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.70,0:12:47.16,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Something else is coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.29,0:12:49.53,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Daichi is in danger?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.85,0:12:51.81,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei, come with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.54,0:12:57.83,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.20,0:13:02.56,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Teppei...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.56,0:13:04.62,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Help Daichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.21,0:13:07.63,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,If I return to that body,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.63,0:13:11.30,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think I'll be able to stay who I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.30,0:13:13.81,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Suck-It-Up Forte!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.21,0:13:20.44,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Quit dilly-dallying!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.83,0:13:22.15,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You need to get this done,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.15,0:13:24.90,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,so we can have our melon tomorrow, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.88,0:13:28.11,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The four of us are eating it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.60,0:13:32.49,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It has to be all four of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.87,0:13:39.00,Default - flashback,D,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow, let's all eat together again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.68,0:13:53.47,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Protect Daichi for me, Teppei...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.78,0:14:10.99,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Amarok, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.26,0:14:17.11,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Another Kiltgang!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.11,0:14:18.16,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Type-1!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.16,0:14:22.73,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}A voice that resounds throughout infinity
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.73,0:14:27.47,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}sings a melody of gentle memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.47,0:14:29.59,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.09,0:14:37.64,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The light of the promise \NI know we once shared.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.81,0:15:01.23,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,These guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.23,0:15:05.34,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,In close quarters, you're at a disadvantage. \NTry to keep your distance, Daichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.03,0:15:19.10,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You're mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.10,0:15:19.77,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Daichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.87,0:15:39.62,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.62,0:15:42.58,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Albion, are you going to betray us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.42,0:15:55.05,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I am your opponent!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.05,0:15:57.43,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Today's the day I devour every last Earthling,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.43,0:15:59.85,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,and snap Albion out of whatever's gotten into him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.34,0:16:01.69,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,And you're first.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.00,0:16:02.64,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.97,0:16:03.60,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Daichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.54,0:16:10.65,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Shoot through both of us, Malkin.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.13,0:16:12.61,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.61,0:16:17.20,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,As long as our Ego Blocks survive, we won't die.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.93,0:16:24.62,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Because you're Albion, you're the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.07,0:16:28.13,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But what about that Earthling?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.73,0:16:32.02,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'll shoot, whether you move or not, Albion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.02,0:16:34.81,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you won't die.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.52,0:16:37.22,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I am Teppei Arashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.74,0:16:44.48,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.25,0:16:47.61,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei Arashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.36,0:16:50.48,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.85,0:16:52.23,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,His Ego Block...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.33,0:17:30.36,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,An Ego Block explosion?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.70,0:17:34.07,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei destroyed his own Ego Block?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.83,0:17:36.05,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.00,0:17:37.78,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.57,0:17:47.17,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That destroyed the vernier thrusters \Non both legs, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.80,0:17:50.16,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have the momentum to take him out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.83,0:17:51.63,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What do I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.63,0:17:56.93,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the one who made Albion crazy, Neoteny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.34,0:17:59.76,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Use this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.11,0:18:01.39,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You know what to do, Daichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.90,0:18:02.97,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,So that's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.98,0:18:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.19,0:18:49.31,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.24,0:19:01.53,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Albion destroyed his own Ego Block.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.37,0:19:03.99,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a hell of a night.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.43,0:19:08.51,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,My Machine Goodfellow broke, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.68,0:19:12.17,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Is Teppei safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.97,0:19:17.63,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,His pulse, temperature, brainwaves, \Nand blood pressure are all nominal...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.40,0:19:20.33,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,For a normal human.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.24,0:19:31.94,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.24,0:19:43.07,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei, what's that in your hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.92,0:19:46.78,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.44,0:19:49.25,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,A Livlaster?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.22,0:19:53.71,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,This is the third one, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.45,0:20:01.13,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Are you canceling the request for \NAkari to be a Kivotos sleeper
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.13,0:20:03.89,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,out of respect for her wishes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.27,0:20:05.65,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,That's part of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.55,0:20:07.85,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,But not everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.85,0:20:12.85,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,You've always been too stubborn \Nto listen to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.85,0:20:16.31,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, her personality is just like yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.94,0:20:19.78,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,My personality isn't as nasty as hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.05,0:20:25.62,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,You've found some hope, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.82,0:20:28.46,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.46,0:20:30.41,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.82,0:20:32.83,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,You're my ex-husband, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.56,0:20:36.66,Default,Y,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave Akari to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.66,0:20:37.75,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.91,0:20:43.71,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I've reported the situation \Nto HQ's Supreme Council,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.71,0:20:46.60,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,and they've agreed to keep it classified for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.21,0:20:50.01,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I got them to allow Hana to stay here, also.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.52,0:20:56.48,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Both HQ and your wife trust \Nyou on a very deep level.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.38,0:20:59.56,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Ex-wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.02,0:21:12.20,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Commander?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.89,0:21:24.86,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Teppei.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.54,0:21:26.54,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.54,0:21:28.20,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You beat Amarok.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.20,0:21:30.19,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You're really amazing, Daichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.74,0:21:33.46,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You keep surprising me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.69,0:21:35.89,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,So here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.14,0:21:48.42,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Daichi Manatsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.49,0:21:51.45,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Teppei Arashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.45,0:21:53.41,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hana Mutou.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.41,0:21:55.37,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Akari Yomatsuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.04,0:22:00.97,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I hereby designate you members of the Globe \NTanegashima base's independent attack force,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.97,0:22:03.09,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,the Midsummer's Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.02,0:22:05.92,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Midsummer's...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.92,0:22:06.92,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Knights?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.23,0:22:10.31,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,"Manatsu" means "Midsummer."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.86,0:22:15.39,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Then that's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.02,0:22:17.61,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Daichi Manatsu,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.61,0:22:21.09,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm officially designating you \Ndriver of the Earth Engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.53,0:22:24.03,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,And you are the leader of this team.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.85,0:22:29.36,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, you are Captain Earth!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.48,0:22:33.33,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What does a captain do?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.15,0:22:37.92,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,For now, let's eat our melons.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.46,0:22:42.96,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,The Midsummer's Knights
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.04,0:24:18.68,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,The Midsummer's Knights \Nbattle the Planetary Gears.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.68,0:24:19.98,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,That's us!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.56,0:24:24.40,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Hana's predictive abilities send \Nus to a casino in Odaiba,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.72,0:24:26.44,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,where we find Amarok and Malkin.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.13,0:24:31.32,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,And a new member of the \NPlanetary Gears awakens.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.72,0:24:34.20,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, on episode 8 of {\i1}Captain Earth{\i0}:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.20,0:24:36.45,Title2,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Sign From the Dark
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.72,0:24:36.45,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Sign From the Dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.81,0:24:39.37,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Engine, scramble!
